The Walt Disney Company has confirmed that its Disney+ streaming service will launch in South Africa in May. In an emailed statement, the group said the service will launch in the country and other territories on 18 May with pricing ser at R119 per month or R1,190 for an annual subscription. The service will launch with exclusive original content and thousands of episodes and movies from Disney, Pixar, Marvel, Star Wars, National Geographic and general entertainment from Star. “Disney+ offers access to high-quality viewing up to four concurrent streams, unlimited downloads on up to ten devices, and the ability to set up to seven different profiles, including the ability for parents to set Kids Profiles that have an easy-to-navigate, child-friendly interface to access age-appropriate content,” the group said. Shows which have already been confirmed at launch, include: The Book of Boba Fett
The Mandalorian
Moon Knight
Shang-Chi and the Legend of The Ten Rings
Luca
Encanto
Cruella
The Simpsons
